Practical example: parsing HTML to extract data

you often want to pull data out of HTML-based sources, like webpages. We‚Äôd call that parsing HTML. Here‚Äôs a mini-example in R:


library(xml2)

"&lt;p&gt;This is some text. This is &lt;b&gt;bold!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" |&gt;
  read_html() |&gt;
  xml_text(trim = TRUE) 

